<section class="bacterial-balance blue-bg">
    <div class="container">
        <h2 class="heading smaller txt-center">
             {{ section.settings.balance_bacteria_heading1 }}
            <br class="d-md-none">
             {{ section.settings.balance_bacteria_heading2 }}
            <br class="d-xs-none" />
             {{ section.settings.balance_bacteria_heading3 }}
            <br class="d-md-none">
             {{ section.settings.balance_bacteria_heading4 }}
        </h2>
        <p class="subtitle  txt-center">
            {{ section.settings.balance_bacteria_para1 }}
        </p>
        <div class="bi-col f-xs-column">
            <div class="left-col">
              {% for block in section.blocks %}
                {% if block.type == 'balance_bacteria_left' %}
                <div class="item">
                    <img src="{{ block.settings.balance_bacteria_left | img_url: '' }}" class="lazyload" width="60"
                        height="62">
                    <p>
                        {{ block.settings.balance_bacteria_para_left }}
                    </p>
                </div>
                  {% endif %}
              {% endfor %}
               {% comment %}
                <div class="item">
                    <img src="{{ 'smoking.svg' | asset_url }}" class="lazyload" width="60"
                        height="62">
                    <p>
                        <b>Hormonal changes</b> from taking birth control, or pregnancy, or even sometimes
                        menstruation.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="item">
                    <img src="{{ 'smoking-2.svg' | asset_url }}" class="lazyload" width="60"
                        height="62">
                    <p>
                        <b> Smoking.</b> Women who smoke, even women exposed to second-hand smoke, are at higher
                        risk for
                        recurrent
                        BV at more than twice the level of non-smokers. Smoking not only weakens your immune
                        system,
                        it
                        actually creates vaginal secretions that attack healthy vaginal lactobacilli and
                        promotes
                        bad
                        bacteria.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="item">
                    <img src="{{ 'glucometer.svg' | asset_url }}" class="lazyload" width="60"
                        height="62">
                    <p>
                        <b>Blood Sugar Issues</b> is a risk factor for Yeast Infections. The reason for this is
                        simple,
                        yeast feeds
                        off of sugar. If diabetes isn't well-controlled, then blood sugar levels can spike. This
                        increase
                        can lead to sugar in your vaginal mucus which causes vaginal candida yeast to grow.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="item">
                    <img src="{{ 'immunity.svg' | asset_url }}" class="lazyload" width="60"
                        height="62">
                    <p>
                        <b>A weak immune system</b> provides an environment for Candida yeast to grow and take
                        over.
                    </p>
                </div>
                {% endcomment %}
            </div>
            <div class="right-col">
              {% for block in section.blocks %}
                {% if block.type == 'balance_bacteria_right' %}
                <div class="item">
                    <img src="{{ block.settings.balance_bacteria_right | img_url: '' }}" class="lazyload" width="60"
                        height="62">
                    <p>
                        {{ block.settings.balance_bacteria_para_right }}
                    </p>
                </div>
                {% endif %}
              {% endfor %}
              {% comment %}
                <div class="item">
                    <img src="{{ 'new-sex.svg' | asset_url }}" class="lazyload" width="60"
                        height="62">
                    <p>
                        <b>Having sex with a new partner.</b> BV is not an STI, however many doctors believe
                        that a
                        new
                        partner's
                        genital chemistry can alter your vaginal bacteria balance enough to trigger BV.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="item">
                    <img src="{{ 'hygine.svg' | asset_url }}" class="lazyload" width="60"
                        height="62">
                    <p>
                        <b>Improper hygiene,</b> such as wiping back to front or having anal then vaginal sex
                        without
                        cleaning up
                        in between.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="item">
                    <img src="{{ 'underwear.svg' | asset_url }}" class="lazyload" width="60"
                        height="62">
                    <p>
                        <b>Leaving tampons or pads in too long</b> can lead to yeast or other infections.

                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="item">
                    <img src="{{ 'tampons.svg' | asset_url }}" class="lazyload" width="60"
                        height="62">
                    <p>
                        <b>Tight underwear or clothes that donâ€™t breathe well</b> create a warm, moist
                        environment.
                        Sitting
                        around
                        in damp sweaty workout clothes or a wet swimsuit is not good either. Candida yeast likes
                        moist and
                        wet.
                    </p>
                </div>
                {% endcomment %}

            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>



